headlines.description: — Joel Embiid clips popped up on social media for a handful of blocked shots he seemed to have against Toronto.
headlines.shortLinkText: Embiid scores 28 points, 76ers beat Raptors 114-99 in first game since Harden trade

events.name: Detroit Pistons at New Orleans Pelicans

headlines.description: — CJ McCollum says he enjoys basketball too much to allow fatigue or a thrown-off routine to stop him from doing what he can to carry the short-handed New Orleans Pelicans through back-to-back games.
headlines.shortLinkText: CJ McCollum scores 33 points to lead short-handed Pelicans past Pistons, 125-116

headlines.description: — Paolo Banchero scored 30 points, making the deciding layup with 14 seconds left, in the Orlando Magic’s 115-113 victory over the Utah Jazz on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Paolo Banchero scores 30 points, Magic beat Jazz 115-113

events.name: San Antonio Spurs at Phoenix Suns

headlines.description: — The San Antonio Spurs were flailing in the fourth quarter Thursday night, struggling to find their footing after the Phoenix Suns erased a 27-point lead and threatened to finish an epic comeback victory.
headlines.shortLinkText: Wembanyama scores 38 points, shines in 4th quarter, as Spurs hold off Suns 132-121

highlights.headline: Wemby drops 38 points in career night in Spurs' win
highlights.description: Victor Wembanyama torches the Suns with 38 points and 10 rebounds to lead the Spurs to a 132-121 win.
